autobrr RSS feed: accept enclosure types that carry parameters after
"application/x-bittorrent" (e.g. "application/x-bittorrent;x-scheme-handler/magnet",
which nekoBT emits). Upstream (v1.80.0 and main) compares with exact equality, so such
enclosures are skipped and the clean magnet in the <enclosure> is never recovered into
MagnetURI -- autobrr then forwards a base-URL-mangled magnet that the *arr clients 404 on.
Matching by prefix lets the existing magnet-recovery (rss.go:163-166) run. See
https://github.com/autobrr/autobrr/blob/v1.80.0/internal/feed/rss.go

--- a/internal/feed/rss.go
+++ b/internal/feed/rss.go
@@ -149,7 +149,7 @@
 			rls.Protocol = domain.ReleaseProtocolNzb
 			break
 		}
-		if e.Type == "application/x-bittorrent" {
+		if strings.HasPrefix(e.Type, "application/x-bittorrent") {
 			if j.Feed.Settings != nil && j.Feed.Settings.DownloadType == domain.FeedDownloadTypeNzb {
 				continue
 			}
